sta Recreation Center</div><div class="activitylisttitle">Junior Youth Spiritual Empowerment Program <br />(Ages 11-15)</div><div class="activitylistdate">Sun Apr 5 10:00AM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="arrian@labahais.org-2015-04-05-10:00-Junior-Youth-Spiritual-Empowerment-Program-(Ages-11-15)" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>One existing and one newly formed junior youth group meet simultaneously in the same location. They identify social forces around them and plan service projects for the betterment of the community. These service projects are combined with healthy recreation (including cooperative sports and games), a study of Baha&#039;i-inspired texts, and complementary activities organized by the junior youth based on their understanding of the curriculum.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Arrian: arrian@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div></div><div class="text-left popoverex activitylistneighborhoodgroups"><div class='activitylistneighborhood'>Martin Luther King Jr / Western</div><div class="activitylisttitle">Junior Youth Spiritual Empowerment Program <br />(Ages 11-12)</div><div class="activitylistdate">Mon Apr 6 5:00PM</div><div class="activitylistdetails"><a id="esperanza@labahais.org-2015-04-06-17:00-Junior-Youth-Spiritual-Empowerment-Program-(Ages-11-12)" tabindex="0" class="btn btn-blue btn-sm" data-toggle="popover" data-trigger="focus" title="Details" data-html="true" data-content="<p>A group of 11-12 yr old youngters get together weekly to study Bahai-inspired curriculum that expands their consciousness and encourages them to think of how they, as a group, can carry out service projects that will improve the commmunity around them. They also play sports and engage in activities inspired by the curriculum they study.</p><p>For more information, please e-mail Esperanza: esperanza@labahais.org</p>">Details</a></div><div class="a